I am proud to join my colleagues Sen. Elizabeth Warren and Sen. Ed Markey in securing $3M in federal funding to renovate the Cosgrove Pool, which is sorely needed, and to keep Lawrence Cosgrove’s legacy alive in Brockton.

Petty Officer Lawrence “Lonnie” Cosgrove, USN was the first resident of Brockton to be killed in action during WWII. He was aboard the USS Reuben James DD-245 when it was torpedoed by a German Submarine on October 31, 1941 off the coast of Iceland.

Expansion of Veterans Included - The PACT Act includes Veterans of the Vietnam, Gulf War & post-9/11 eras.

Expansion of Locations Included - In addition to added presumptive conditions, locations were added for burn pits, Agent Orange, radiation, asbestos & other toxic exposure.

You Can Resubmit Your Claim - If you were previously denied a VA disability claim for a condition related to toxic exposures or one that is now included in the new list of presumptive conditions, you can resubmit your claim.

Deadlines - The deadline for Veterans to apply for retroactive benefits under the PACT Act is August 9th, 2023. Veterans can still apply for PACT Act benefits after August 9th but they won’t be backdated. Click this link to file now: va.gov/resources/the-pact-ac…

The PACT Act is the most significant increase in Veteran benefits in history that went into effect in January 2023.
